com.spotify.sdk.android.playback

Class Config

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.spotify.sdk.android.playback.Config

  • public final class Config
extends Object
    This class is used to pass configuration parameters to the native SDK layer. At the moment, the developer does not need to directly use this class, as the information in it can be automatically determined from the system, though that may change at some point in the future.

    • Nested Class Summary

      Nested Classes 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      static class  Config.DeviceType
      The SDK represents device types as raw integers, but rather than dealing with an enum an abstract class is used, as we are missing some intermediate values and require a bit more granularity here than an enum can offer.

      • displayName

        public String displayName
        Device's display name.
        In case of this SDK the application's name as defined in the android:label field in the <application> element in AndroidManifest.xml file.
        If no name is present it will fall back to the name of the model of the device (e.g. Nexus 5)
        It is also possible to overwrite this property if it should be something else.

      • brandName

        public final String brandName
        Device's brand name. In case of this SDK this should be a client ID that the app is using.

      • modelName

        public final String modelName
        Device's model name. In case of this SDK this will be automatically set to application's package.

    • Method Detail

      • useCache

        public void useCache(boolean useCache)
        Use disk cache.
        Disabling this setting will turn off the disk cache. When disk cache is enabled streamed songs are cached locally and read from disk when played again.
        Disk cache is turned on by default.
        Please note that currently it only uses default file storage to save files.
        Parameters:
        useCache - If true disk cache will be used, if false played songs will not be cached.

      • shouldUseCache

        public boolean shouldUseCache()
        Check if disk cache is turned on.
        Returns:
        true if cache is being used, false if it is not.
